ep learning\\ud83d\\udca1\",\n    \"author\": \"wngus_\",\n    \"total_votes\": 206,\n    \"last_run_time\": \"2023-07-02T08:18:52.897000Z\",\n    \"is_private\": false,\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:21.295263Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"ref\": \"eisgandar/spaceship-titanic-eda-xgboost-80\",\n    \"title\": \"\\ud83c\\udf0c Spaceship Titanic - EDA & XGBoost- 80%+\",\n    \"author\": \"Mustanger\",\n    \"total_votes\": 182,\n    \"last_run_time\": \"2022-12-01T15:52:39.440000Z\",\n    \"is_private\": false,\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:21.295272Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"ref\": \"usharengaraju/tensorflow-spaceship-neuraldecisionforests\",\n    \"title\": \"\\ud83d\\ude80\\ud83d\\ude80[TensorFlow]SpaceShip - NeuralDecisionForests\",\n    \"author\": \"Tensor Girl\",\n    \"total_votes\": 180,\n    \"last_run_time\": \"2022-02-25T01:30:11.367000Z\",\n    \"is_private\": false,\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:21.295279Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"ref\": \"ruchi798/spaceship-titanic-eda-pytorch-baseline-w-b\",\n    \"title\": \"\\ud83d\\ude80 Spaceship Titanic: EDA + PyTorch Baseline + W&B\",\n    \"author\": \"Ruchi Bhatia\",\n    \"total_votes\": 180,\n    \"last_run_time\": \"2022-03-24T05:04:08.487000Z\",\n    \"is_private\": false,\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:21.295287Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"ref\": \"bhatnagardaksh/gradient-descent-from-scratch\",\n    \"title\": \"Gradient Descent from scratch\",\n    \"author\": \"Daksh Bhatnagar\",\n    \"total_votes\": 174,\n    \"last_run_time\": \"2024-11-09T03:54:38.250000Z\",\n    \"is_private\": false,\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:21.295292Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"ref\": \"cv13j0/spaceship-titanic-nn-model-feature-eng\",\n    \"title\": \"\\ud83c\\udf20 Spaceship Titanic NN Model + Feature Eng.\",\n    \"author\": \"C4rl05/V\",\n    \"total_votes\": 167,\n    \"last_run_time\": \"2023-11-12T21:21:03.430000Z\",\n    \"is_private\": false,\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:21.296280Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"ref\": \"fernaandodantas/lgbm-0-8066-score-top-7-solution\",\n    \"title\": \"LGBM 0.8066% Score Top 7% Solution\",\n    \"author\": \"Fernando Dantas\",\n    \"total_votes\": 164,\n    \"last_run_time\": \"2024-02-28T00:02:06Z\",\n    \"is_private\": false,\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:21.296290Z\"\n  }\n]\n[\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 309323,\n    \"title\": \"Welcome to the Spaceship Titanic!\",\n    \"author\": \"Ryan Holbrook\",\n    \"author_username\": \"ryanholbrook\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"STAFF\",\n    \"votes\": 220,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"Welcome to the **Spaceship Titanic**!\\n\\nThe dataset is a bit bigger and the features a bit more complex, but this competition has everything you love about the original [**Titanic - Machine Learning from Disaster**](https://www.kaggle.com/c/titanic) -- this time *in space*!\\n\\nThere's a lot to discover in this dataset. Check out some of our [free courses](https://www.kaggle.com/learn) if you'd like to brush up on the fundamentals:\\n- [Python](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/python) for first steps with programming\\n- [Intro to Machine Learning](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/intro-to-machine-learning) for learning what it's all about\\n- [Pandas](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/pandas) on using Python's most popular library for manipulating tabular data\\n- [Intermediate Machine Learning](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/intermediate-machine-learning) on essential competition skills like categorical encoding and cross-validation\\n- [Data Visualization](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/data-visualization) for discovering relationships in the dataset\\n- [Feature Engineering](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/feature-engineering) on how to improve performance by creating more informative inputs\\n- [Intro to Deep Learning](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/intro-to-deep-learning) to discover neural networks\\n\\nBe sure to share your discoveries with a public notebook or here in the discussion forum.\\n\\nHappy Kaggling!\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309323\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-02-22T22:22:39.047565300Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2026-05-25T13:49:41.816666700Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023598Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 429952,\n    \"title\": \"This Competition has an Official Discord Channel\",\n    \"author\": \"Myles O'Neill\",\n    \"author_username\": \"mylesoneill\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"STAFF\",\n    \"votes\": 101,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"In addition to this competition forum, you can continue the discussion in our official Kaggle Discord Server here: [discord.gg/kaggle](http://discord.gg/kaggle)\\n\\nThe Discord is a great place to ask getting started questions, chat about the nuances of this competition, and connect with potential team mates. Learn more about Discord at our [announcement here](https://www.kaggle.com/discussions/general/429933). Here are a few things to keep in mind though:\\n\\n**1. Discord Competition Channels are 'Public'**\\nDiscord channels for specific competitions are considered 'public' spaces where you are allowed to talk about competition details (it will not count as private sharing).\\n\\n**2. Discord Competition Channels are Not Monitored by Staff**\\nKaggle Staff and Hosts running competitions will not monitor Discord or be available to answer questions in Discord. Always post important questions in the forums.\\n\\n**3. Keep the Good Stuff on the Forums**\\nPlease keep important questions, insights, writeups, and other valuable conversation on the Kaggle forums. Discord is intended to be a more casual space to discuss competitions and help each other, we want to keep all the best information on the forums.\\n\\n**4. Remember to never privately share competition code or data**\\nPlease remember that private sharing of competition code or data is, as always, not permitted. Code sharing must always be done publicly through the Kaggle forums/notebooks.\\n\\nI hope you\\u2019ll join us to chat on Discord soon!\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/429952\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2023-08-07T19:03:08.251357200Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-07T17:52:07.233333300Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023623Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 315987,\n    \"title\": \"Some rules to fill NaNs\",\n    \"author\": \"Vincent Debout\",\n    \"author_username\": \"vdebout\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"MASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 99,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"I denote \\\"Children\\\", persons with age <= 12 years old.\\n\\nHere are some rules I identified to fill NaNs:\\n\\n- link between HomePlanet and CabinDeck:\\n    Earth on E, F,G\\n    Mars on D, E, F\\n    Europa on A, B, C, D, E, T\\n- persons in the same group all have the same CabinSide, possibly on different CabinDeck\\n- in groups with several CabinDeck, people with no bill are necessarily on CabinDeck:\\n   Earth on G\\n   Europa on B\\n   Mars on E or F\\n- for Europa groups with several CabinDeck, people with no bill are on deck B\\n- CabinNum are in increasing order of PassengerIdGroup for each (CabinDeck, CabinSide)\\n  => This is very useful but need a complex algorithm. All Cabins are occupied ! \\n- People in a group have the same HomePlanet\\n- Surnames are found in a unique HomePlanet\\n- Children have no bill\\n- CryoSleep have no bill\\n- People not Children and not CryoSleep with no bill all have Destination TRAPPIST-1e\\n- link between HomePlanet, VIP (also Age and CryoSleep):\\n   Earth no VIP\\n   Mars VIP have Age >= 18 and no CryoSleep and never goes to \\\"55 Cancri e\\\"\\n   Europa VIP have Age >= 25\\n- Europa with Age < 25 never goes to \\\"PSO J318.5-22\\\"\\n- Mars children are all transported\\n\\nApproximative rules (with some exceptions):\\n- Firstnames are found in a unique HomePlanet\\n- ToTal bill has minimum per HomePlanet and CabinDeck (Earth is around 300, Mars 400 and Europa 1000), be careful when filling with median\\n\\n\\nPlease let me know if you identify additionnal rules\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/315987\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-03-30T16:58:04.683729200Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2025-05-01T03:32:59.423333300Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023635Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 309318,\n    \"title\": \"Looking for a Team Thread\",\n    \"author\": \"Ashley Chow\",\n    \"author_username\": \"ashleychow\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"EXPERT\",\n    \"votes\": 61,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"Use this thread to find a teammate if you're interested in finding others to work with!\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309318\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-02-22T21:55:36.942784700Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2026-03-16T19:49:58.666666700Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023644Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 316768,\n    \"title\": \"Feature engineering results\",\n    \"author\": \"Samuel Cortinhas\",\n    \"author_username\": \"samuelcortinhas\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"GRANDMASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 55,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"Here is a summary of the **feature engineering** I have tried so far and the results I got on the test set. The baseline I used can be found in my notebook [here](https://www.kaggle.com/code/samuelcortinhas/spaceship-titanic-a-complete-guide). All I did was add/drop 1 feature at a time and see how the final score changed.\\n\\n* drop **VIP** feature - 0.02% increase\\n* create an **expenditure** feature that sums the total money spent across the 5 amenities - 0.5% increase\\n* create expenditure feature and drop the 5 amenities (**RoomService**, ...,**VRDeck**) - 4.7% decrease\\n* create a **cabin deck** feature (A,B,...,T) - 0.35% increase\\n* create a **cabin side** feature (P/S) - 0.9% increase \\n* create a **group size** feature from the PassengerId column - 0.1% increase\\n* create a **no spending** binary feature that is 1 if no money was spent and 0 otherwise - 0.2% increase\\n* Create a **solo** feature that tracks if passenger was travelling on their own (from PassengerId) - 0.2% increase\\n* Create **cabin region** features according to chunks of 300 passengers (see [here](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/316379) for details) - 0.2% increase\\n* create a **family size** feature from last name - 0.0% change\\n* create binary **age** features for 0-18 yo, 18-25 yo, 25+ yo - 0.02% increase\\n* same as above but drop the **age** column - 0.4% drop\\n\\n**Conclusions:**\\n* create total expenditure, cabin deck and cabin side features - these are very helpful\\n* group size, solo, no_spending and cabin regions also help a bit\\n\\nDo you agree? What feature engineering have you tried and did it improve your score?\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/316768\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-04-03T18:24:50.078984100Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2025-06-10T04:03:09.240Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023671Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 309317,\n    \"title\": \"New to Machine Learning or Kaggle?\",\n    \"author\": \"Ashley Chow\",\n    \"author_username\": \"ashleychow\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"EXPERT\",\n    \"votes\": 53,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"New to machine learning and data science? No question is too basic or too simple. Feel free to start your own thread, or use this thread as a place to post any first-timer clarifying questions for the Kaggle community to help you with!\\n\\nIf you would consider yourself a beginner but don't know where to get started, let other Kagglers help you take your first steps here!\\n\\nNew to Kaggle? Take a look at a few videos our very own Dr. Rachael Tatman has put together to learn a bit more about [site etiquette](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aIus8si_Et0), [Kaggle lingo](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEJHyuWKd-s), and [how to enter a competition using Kaggle Notebooks](https://www.youtube.com/watch?&v=GJBOMWpLpTQ).\\n\\n**Remember:** Kaggle is for everyone. Whether you're teaming up or sharing tips in the competition forum, we expect everyone to follow our [Kaggle community guidelines](https://www.kaggle.com/community-guidelines).\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309317\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-02-22T21:54:54.307547200Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2025-07-27T07:09:15.040Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023680Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 309803,\n    \"title\": \"How to Choose OneHotEncoding between LabelEncoding? I'll Answer!! (EDA Tip)\",\n    \"author\": \"Wongi Park\",\n    \"author_username\": \"kalelpark\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"MASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 44,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"We apply One-Hot Encoding when:\\n1. The Categorical feature is not ordinal\\n2. The number of categorical features is less so one-hot encoding can be effectively applied\\n\\nWe apply Label Encoding when:\\n\\n1. The categorical feature is ordinal (like Primary school, high school)\\n2. The number of categories is quite large as one-hot encoding can lead to high memory consumption\\n<hr>\\n\\nOne-Hot-Encoding Feature\\n- HomePlanet\\n- CryoSleep\\n- Cabin (Side)\\n- Destination\\n- VIP\\n\\nLabel Encoding Feature\\n- Cabin(Deck)\\n- Name    (cause.2)   (many nuinque values)\\n\\n<hr>\\nWe can think about new Feature about Total bill!\\n\\nTotal Bill = 'RoomService' +  'FoodCourt' + 'ShoppingMall '+ 'Spa' + 'VRDeck'\\n* We need to deal with NaN values Before adding them.\\n(NaN values replace 0 beacuse,  It's most common in data.)\\n\\nIf you helpful, Don't forget vote!\\nModel tip : https://www.kaggle.com/c/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309535\\n\\nCode : https://www.kaggle.com/kalelpark/spaceship-titanic-solutions-for-beginner\\n(Code will be Update!)\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309803\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-02-25T16:17:53.392291300Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2025-05-07T14:39:16.120Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023690Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 386628,\n    \"title\": \"Starter materials\",\n    \"author\": \"Ravi Ramakrishnan\",\n    \"author_username\": \"ravi20076\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"GRANDMASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 44,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"Hello all,\\n\\nWishing you the best for the challenge! The assignment appears to be a binary classifier, from the target, we infer that the classes are fairly balanced. \\n\\nHope the below starter materials are useful to quickly onboard-\\n\\n**Column descriptions**\\n\\n1. Booking_ID: unique identifier of each booking\\n2. No of adults: Number of adults\\n3. No of children: Number of Children\\n4. noofweekend_nights: Number of weekend nights (Saturday or Sunday) the guest stayed or booked to stay at the hotel\\n5. noofweek_nights: Number of week nights (Monday to Friday) the guest stayed or booked to stay at the hotel\\n6. typeofmeal_plan: Type of meal plan booked by the customer:\\n7. requiredcarparking_space: Does the customer require a car parking space? (0 - No, 1- Yes)\\n8. roomtypereserved: Type of room reserved by the customer. The values are ciphered (encoded) by INN Hotels.\\n9. lead_time: Number of days between the date of booking and the arrival date\\n10. arrival_year: Year of arrival date\\n11. arrival_month: Month of arrival date\\n12. arrival_date: Date of the month\\n13. Market segment type: Market segment designation.\\n14. repeated_guest: Is the customer a repeated guest? (0 - No, 1- Yes)\\n15. noofprevious_cancellations: Number of previous bookings that were canceled by the customer prior to the current booking\\n16. noofpreviousbookingsnot_canceled: Number of previous bookings not canceled by the customer prior to the current booking\\n17. avgpriceper_room: Average price per day of the reservation; prices of the rooms are dynamic. (in euros)\\n18. noofspecial_requests: Total number of special requests made by the customer (e.g. high floor, view from the room, etc)\\n19. **booking_status: Flag indicating if the booking was canceled or not** -- target\\n\\n**Original data link**-\\n\\nhttps://www.kaggle.com/datasets/gauravduttakiit/reservation-cancellation-prediction\\n\\n**General information on the competition metric- AUC/ GINI curve**\\n\\n1. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gini_coefficient -- wikipedia article\\n2. https://developers.google.com/machine-learning/crash-course/classification/roc-and-auc -- short and terse article on the measure\\n3. https://towardsdatascience.com/understanding-auc-roc-curve-68b2303cc9c5 -- well curated GINI related article\\n4. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OAl6eAyP-yo -- introductory YouTube video for the GINI measure\\n5. https://acutecaretesting.org/en/articles/roc-curves-what-are-they-and-how-are-they-used -- another great article on the GINI measure\\n\\n**Recent TPS binary classifiers**\\n\\nMy below discussion post highlights a few binary classifiers from the past year's edition of the playground series and some useful resources for the same- \\nhttps://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s3e2/discussion/377171\\n\\n**Playground Season 3 binary classifier resources**\\n\\nThe below kernels could be of use, based on recent season 3 problems with the same metric too-\\n\\n**Episode2**\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/dmitryuarov/ps-s3e2-catboost-lasso-nn-fiasco -- popular kernel from Playground Season3- Episode2\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/tilii7/modeling-stroke-dataset-with-lasso-regression -- uses a LASSO regression to predict the target, it could be an alternative approach to the problem too\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/sergiosaharovskiy/ps-s3e2-2023-eda-and-base-pytorch-model -- uses PyTorch to great effect and is a very beginner friendly kernel\\n\\n**Episode3**\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/phongnguyen1/s3e3-from-eda-to-final-submission -- comprehensive kernel highlighting an effective process flow from EDA-submission to great effect\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/samuelcortinhas/ps-s3e3-hill-climbing-like-a-gm -- great kernel explaining **hill climbing** ensemble strategy to blend predictions\\n6. https://www.kaggle.com/code/alexandershumilin/ps-s3-e3-ensemble-model-woe-encoding-optuna -- great kernel, explaining the usage of various model approaches with tuning using optuna also\\n\\n**General kernels for binary classification**\\n\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/ravi20076/titanic-eda-model-custompipelines -- titanic binary classifier with EDA and custom pipelines with an array of model options\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/startupsci/titanic-data-science-solutions/comments -- one of the best Titanic classifier tutorials on Kaggle with beginner friendly code and lots of comments and explanations\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/prashant111/naive-bayes-classifier-in-python -- excellent beginner friendly notebook highlighting the naive bayes method on an approachable dataset\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/prashant111/decision-tree-classifier-tutorial -- excellent Decision Tree tutorial notebook with lots of explanations, comments and fantastic visuals and tree diagrams\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/willkoehrsen/start-here-a-gentle-introduction -- excellent notebook on an approachable dataset and use-case with good quality EDA, great visuals and a well drafted baseline logistic model, perfect starter for a competition\\n6. https://www.kaggle.com/code/devsubhash/tps-august-eda-failure-prediction -- excellent EDA and classical ML based approach on a very beginner friendly dataset\\n7. https://www.kaggle.com/code/ambrosm/tpsaug22-eda-which-makes-sense -- excellent EDA oriented notebook for an approachable use-case and basic ML models, apt for a beginner to start and onboard onto ML assignments\\n8. https://www.kaggle.com/code/samuelcortinhas/spaceship-titanic-a-complete-guide -- great visuals, good EDA and simple models on an approachable starter competition use-case. This is an ideal starter notebook for the competition and is highly beginner friendly\\n\\nBest regards and happy learning!\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/386628\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2023-02-14T00:23:00.936215500Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2023-02-27T17:32:28.043333300Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023703Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 309693,\n    \"title\": \"Tip - Don't forget about the Cabin! \\ud83d\\udcc8\",\n    \"author\": \"Alex Teboul\",\n    \"author_username\": \"alexteboul\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"EXPERT\",\n    \"votes\": 38,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"For a slight **increase in accuracy**, don't drop the **Cabin** column entirely from your modeling.\\n\\n**For example:**\\n```\\n# split column and add new columns to df\\ntrain[['Deck', 'Num', 'Side']] = train['Cabin'].str.split('/', expand=True)\\n# display the dataframe\\ntrain.head()\\n```\\n\\n[![Screen-Shot-2022-02-24-at-4-07-00-PM.png](https://i.postimg.cc/BQ8rqMQH/Screen-Shot-2022-02-24-at-4-07-00-PM.png)](https://postimg.cc/RNBsd1tZ)\\n\\n## [Notebook Link](https://www.kaggle.com/alexteboul/space-titanic-eda-models-lb-0-799l)\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309693\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-02-24T22:19:11.164984300Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2024-07-08T14:13:09.266666700Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023712Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 563105,\n    \"title\": \"[Suggestion] - Kindly consider organizing few playground episodes for beginners/ new accounts only\",\n    \"author\": \"Ravi Ramakrishnan\",\n    \"author_username\": \"ravi20076\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"GRANDMASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 35,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"Hello Kaggle team,\\n\\nI am sure we all concur that the Playground Series competitions are developed to provide a conduit to beginners to onboard into Kaggle and step up from starter assignments like the Titanic challenge and Spaceship Titanic assignment and then eventually to attempt featured and research assignments. The image from an older playground episode corroborates this - \\n\\n![](https://www.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/kaggle-forum-message-attachments/o/inbox%2F8273630%2F53cd6fc27efc08115687045e8b7f0528%2FPlayground.png?generation=1739606695039387&alt=media)\\n\\nConsidering this, I may suggest to Kaggle to consider organizing a few episodes in the year **only for beginners**, the real consumer of the series. Perhaps the following participant base may be considered - \\n1. Include people with new Kaggle accounts in the past 6 months \\n2. Include people with 1-3 attempts at the playground series, please consider excluding participants winning past episodes to direct the said episodes for newcomers  \\n3. Exclude Masters and Grandmasters across all tiers in these episodes\\n4. Include participants in the age group of 15-20 / students if data is available \\n5. Include anyone else who identifies himself/ herself as a beginner as per Kaggle's discretion \\n\\nPerhaps organizing a CPU-only code competition for this participant group will also place them at the same level in terms of resources and orient them effectively into code submissions in other competitions. Perhaps, this will also provide a fresh learning perspective for others like me with a long experience in the series and on Kaggle in general. \\n\\nRegards. \",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/563105\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2025-02-15T08:09:04.498714200Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2025-02-26T22:29:10.136666700Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023721Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 332081,\n    \"title\": \"A Summary of all top discussion posts\",\n    \"author\": \"The Devastator\",\n    \"author_username\": \"thedevastator\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"GRANDMASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 26,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"## A Summary of all top discussion posts\\nBelow is a summary of all the top discussion posts of this competition so far. \\nMade by myself. \\n_____\\n\\n\\n[Make the best use of \\\"Deck\\\" feature](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/310238) \\nby [mostafaalaa123](mostafaalaa123)\\n\\n- From the comments:\\n- I think the idea is to create a new feature that is 1 if the deck is safe and 0 if it is dangerous.\\n\\n[\\\"Gender\\\" didn't help me](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/310239) \\nby [mostafaalaa123](mostafaalaa123)\\n\\n- Adding gender as a feature didn't help the author's model.\\n\\n[Spaceship Titanic Compare BaseModels EveryBody Get Insight!](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309535)\\nby [kalelpark](kalelpark)\\n\\nThe author used pycaret to compere many models to try and find the best one. These were the results:\\n\\n![](https://i.ibb.co/26xKhJd/2022-02-24-094651.jpg)\\n\\n**Top 5 Models**\\n- LightGBM - 79.1%\\n- GradientBoostingClassifier - 79.6%\\n- AdaBoostClassifier - 79.4%\\n- RandomForest - 79.2%\\n- CatBoost - 79.6%\\n\\n[Question - How to deal with this kind of distribution ?](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/310009) \\nby [kartik2khandelwal](kartik2khandelwal)\\n\\n- The author was looking at the distribution of some of the features and asked for guidance about dealing with such a distribution.\\n\\n**Options proposed**\\n- **Remove Outliers** - but this will result in less data\\n- **Perform some transformation technique** - log, sqrt, boxcox and so on\\u2026\\n- **Make it a categorical variable** by putting all the outliers as 0 and other data as 1 - may leads to less information.\\n\\n**From the comments**\\n\\n- **Remove Outliers** - I would advise not to do so. Usually, if we remove outliers it is because we make the hypothesis that the event is due to some kind of artifact (a wrong record). But here, people paying a lot is not a wrong record and it could actually be valuable data.\\n- **Perform some transformation** - Every variable is not meant to be normally distributed. I think we can even expect this variable to be distributed as shown as we would expect only a few amounts of people to be able to spend that much. If you use log transform, for example, you will only compress your data and lose most of the value it holds. Except if you need to approximate a normal distribution for analysis purposes, or because you need to satisfy the normal distribution hypothesis for one of your processing steps, I would suggest not to.\\n- **Make it a categorical variable** - As discussed previously, we can't really talk of outliers here. An outlier is a record that seems abnormal based on the hypothesis of the distribution it follows. So, I would suggest not applying this categorical transformation either.\\n\\n- **Perform some transformation** One could use a non-parametric estimator, such as decision trees or developments thereof, such as RandomForest, XGBoost, or HistGradientBoostingClassifier etc. thus obviating the need to transform the features to become Gaussian.\\n- **Make it a categorical variable** Rather than actually replacing the feature as a categorical variable, create a new additional feature as a categorical variable, perhaps with something like\\n\\n- `df['food_spending'] = np.where(df['FoodCourt'] > 1000, 'yes', 'no')`\\n\\n\\n[[Exploratory Data Analysis] High cardinality &amp; High correlation](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309513) \\nby [rishirajacharya](rishirajacharya)\\n\\nThe author is sharing some findings of EDA:\\n\\n- `PassengerId` has a high cardinality: 8693 distinct values\\n- `Cabin` has a high cardinality: 6560 distinct values\\n- `Name` has a high cardinality: 8473 distinct values\\n- `FoodCourt` is highly correlated with VRDeck`\\n- `CryoSleep` is highly correlated with `Transported`\\n- `HomePlanet` is highly correlated with `Destination`\\n\\n[Tip - Don't forget about the Cabin! \\ud83d\\udcc8](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309693)\\nby [alexteboul](alexteboul)\\n\\n- From the post: \\\"For a slight **increase in accuracy**, don't drop the `Cabin` column entirely from your modeling.\\\"\\n\\n**For Example**\\n```python\\n# split column and add new columns to df\\ntrain[['Deck', 'Num', 'Side']] = train['Cabin'].str.split('/', expand=True)\\n# display the dataframe\\ntrain.head()\\n```\\n- [notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/alexteboul/space-titanic-eda-models-lb-0-799l)\\n\\n[How to Choose OneHotEncoding between LabelEncoding? I'll Answer!! (EDA Tip)](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309803) \\nby [kalelpark](kalelpark)\\n\\n- From the post:\\n\\n**We apply One-Hot Encoding when:**\\n\\n- The Categorical feature is not ordinal\\n- The number of categorical features is less so one-hot encoding can be effectively applied\\n\\n**We apply Label Encoding when:**\\n- The categorical feature is ordinal (like Primary school, high school)\\n- The number of categories is quite large as one-hot encoding can lead to high memory consumption\\n\\nThe author also shared a public [notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/kalelpark/spaceship-titanic-solutions-for-beginner)\\n\\n[Might be a good way to fill some missing  value?](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/310574) \\nby [gargantuar](gargantuar)\\n\\n- Found that for the passenger when the first part of the PassengerId is same ,the Homeplanet ,Cabin are also same.\\n- So, we can fill some missing value of these two values(about 50 in total 200),that might be able to improve the data quality.\\n\\n[Adding GENDER Feature based on NAME column](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309664) \\nby [sardorabdirayimov](sardorabdirayimov)\\n\\n- The notebook uses an [external web page](https://www.gpeters.com/names/baby-names.php) to identify gender based on the name\\n- Also: `Name` column in the dataset definitely helps to identify `gender`, `family`, `nationality` , `personality`\\n\\n\\n[\\ud83d\\udccc EDA\\ud83d\\udcc8 + FE\\ud83d\\udd25 + Comparison\\u2696\\ufe0f + Pseudo\\ud83c\\udfad](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309626) \\nby [hasanbasriakcay](hasanbasriakcay)\\n\\n- **Shared multiple notebooks:**\\n- [EDA](https://www.kaggle.com/hasanbasriakcay/spaceship-titanic-eda-fe-baseline)\\n- [Model Comparison](https://www.kaggle.com/hasanbasriakcay/spaceship-titanic-pycaret-model-comparisons)\\n- [Pseudo Labeling](https://www.kaggle.com/hasanbasriakcay/spaceship-titanic-pseudo-labels-stacking)\\n\\n[Cabin Feature is more IMPORTANT than you believe](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/319152)\\nby [javigallego](javigallego)\\n\\n- Sharing a code snippet for splitting the Cabin feature into 3 new features.\\n```python\\ndef split_Cabin(df):\\n    df['Deck'] = df['Cabin'].str.split(\\\"/\\\", n=2, expand=True)[0]\\n    df['Number'] = df['Cabin'].str.split(\\\"/\\\", n=2, expand=True)[1]\\n    df['Side'] = df['Cabin'].str.split(\\\"/\\\", n=2, expand=True)[2]\\n    df.pop('Cabin')\\n    return df\\n```\\n\\n[Feature engineering results](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/316768)\\nby [samuelcortinhas](samuelcortinhas)\\n\\n**Sharing the results of Feature Engineering:**\\n- drop VIP feature - 0.02% increase\\n- create an expenditure feature that sums the total money spent across the 5 amenities - 0.5% increase\\n- create expenditure feature and drop the 5 amenities (RoomService, \\u2026,VRDeck) - 4.7% decrease\\n- create a cabin deck feature (A,B,\\u2026,T) - 0.35% increase\\n- create a cabin side feature (P/S) - 0.9% increase\\n- create a group size feature from the PassengerId column - 0.1% increase\\n- create a no spending binary feature that is 1 if no money was spent and 0 otherwise - 0.2% increase\\n- Create a solo feature that tracks if passenger was travelling on their own (from PassengerId) - 0.2% increase\\n- Create cabin region features according to chunks of 300 passengers (see here for details) - 0.2% increase-\\n- create a family size feature from last name - 0.0% change\\n- create binary age features for 0-18 yo, 18-25 yo, 25+ yo - 0.02% increase\\n- same as above but drop the age column - 0.4% drop\\n\\n**Conclusions:**\\n- create total expenditure, cabin deck and cabin side features - these are very helpful\\n- group size, solo, no_spending and cabin regions also help a bit\\n\\n[full notebook here](https://www.kaggle.com/code/samuelcortinhas/spaceship-titanic-a-complete-guide)\\n\\n[Cabin number chunking](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/316379) \\nby [samuelcortinhas](samuelcortinhas)\\n\\n- From the post: \\\"It seems that the cabin number is chunked into groups of 300 cabins, and within each group the target distribution is a little bit different.\\\"\\n![](https://i.postimg.cc/NjpRsTXT/Cabin-number-distribution.png)\\n\\n\\n[Speed up your kernel using Intel\\u00ae Extension for Scikit-learn](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/314402) \\nby [lordozvlad](lordozvlad)\\n\\n-From the post: \\\"If you want to speed up your kernel you can use Intel\\u00ae Extension for Scikit-learn!\\\"\\n```python\\n!pip install scikit-learn-intelex\\n```\\n- [notebook:  Introduction to scikit-learn-intelex](https://www.kaggle.com/lordozvlad/introduction-to-scikit-learn-intelex/notebook)\\n\\n[\\ud83d\\ude80 Spaceship Titanic 0.79962 \\ud83d\\ude80](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/312497) \\nby [rocklen](rocklen)\\n\\n- Sharing a [notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/code/rocklen/spaceship-titanic-2-0-80079) with a score of 0.79962 using XGBoost + Randomized Search\\n\\n[Random Forest Perform significantly better in some cases than XGBoost](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/314044)\\nby [shivamnegi1993](shivamnegi1993)\\n\\n- Random Forest is performing better than XGBoost in some cases.\\n- Check cases on the original thread.\\n\\n[Some rules to fill NaNs](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/315987) \\nby [vdebout](vdebout)\\n\\n- The author shared some hardcoded rules to fill NaNs.\\n\\n- link between HomePlanet and CabinDeck:\\n    Earth on E, F,G\\n    Mars on D, E, F\\n    Europa on A, B, C, D, E, T\\n- persons in the same group all have the same CabinSide, possibly on different CabinDeck\\n    in groups with several CabinDeck, people with no bill are necessarily on CabinDeck:\\n    Earth on G\\n    Europa on B\\n    Mars on E or F\\n- for Europa groups with several CabinDeck, people with no bill are on deck B\\n- CabinNum are in increasing order of PassengerIdGroup for each (CabinDeck, CabinSide) => This is very useful but need a complex algorithm. All Cabins are occupied !\\n- People in a group have the same HomePlanet\\n- Surnames are found in a unique HomePlanet\\n- Children have no bill\\n- CryoSleep have no bill\\n- People not Children and not CryoSleep with no bill all have Destination TRAPPIST-1e\\n- link between HomePlanet, VIP (also Age and CryoSleep):\\n    Earth no VIP\\n    Mars VIP have Age >= 18 and no CryoSleep and never goes to \\\"55 Cancri e\\\"\\n    Europa VIP have Age >= 25\\n    Europa with Age < 25 never goes to \\\"PSO J318.5-22\\\"\\n    Mars children are all transported\\n\\n**Approximative rules (with some exceptions):**\\n- Firstnames are found in a unique HomePlanet\\n- ToTal bill has minimum per HomePlanet and CabinDeck (Earth is around 300, Mars 400 and Europa 1000), be careful when filling with median\\n\\n\\n[Tip. Increase your score!](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/312173) \\nby [michael6141](michael6141)\\n\\n- Sharing a tip to increase your score: \\\"Try to average received probabilities on each validation split (list(probabilities)/len(probabilities)), predict_proba may help you. Averaging the model is a powerful tool to get a high validation score.\\\"\\n\\n[[Exploratory Data Analysis] Missing Values](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309514)\\nby [rishirajacharya](rishirajacharya)\\n\\n- Age has 179 (2.1%) missing values\\n- Destination has 182 (2.1%) missing values\\n- FoodCourt has 183 (2.1%) missing values\\n- HomePlanet has 201 (2.3%) missing values\\n- Spa has 183 (2.1%) missing values\\n- VIP has 203 (2.3%) missing values\\n- RoomService has 181 (2.1%) missing values\\n- VRDeck has 188 (2.2%) missing values\\n- Name has 200 (2.3%) missing values\\n- From the post:\\n- Cabin has 199 (2.3%) missing values\\n- ShoppingMall has 208 (2.4%) missing values\\n- CryoSleep has 217 (2.5%) missing values\\n\\n- Sharing a [public notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/rishirajacharya/spaceship-titanic-detailed) about the missing values in the dataset.\\n\\n[[Spaceship Titanic] TensorFlow Extended - Towards ML Engineering ](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/328882)\\nby [usharengaraju](usharengaraju)\\n\\n- Sharing in depth analysis of the dataset using TensorFlow.\\n- Sharing a [public notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/harshjain123/time-series-arima-sarima) about the following time series concepts:\\n\\n\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/332081\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-06-20T09:06:34.291829800Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2022-06-22T15:28:53.153333300Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023747Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 309319,\n    \"title\": \"Rolling Leaderboards\",\n    \"author\": \"Ashley Chow\",\n    \"author_username\": \"ashleychow\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"EXPERT\",\n    \"votes\": 24,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"This competition is a *Getting Started* competition, meaning that it will not have a set deadline. As the competition grows, we want to ensure it does not outgrow its own leaderboard!\\n\\nTo keep with the spirit of getting-started competitions, we will implement a two month rolling window on submissions. Once a submission is more than two months old, it will be invalidated and no longer count towards the leaderboard. If your team has no submissions in the previous two months, the team will also drop from the leaderboard. This will keep the leaderboard at a manageable size, freshen it up, and prevent newcomers from getting lost in a sea of abandoned scores. \\n\\nTo quote @wcukierski: \\\"Consider this a change to be more like a college class: your professor decides the curve based on how your classmates score, not based on all exam scores since 1986.\\\"\\n\\n*\\\"I worked so hard to get that score! What happened to it!?!\\\"*\\n\\nGetting started competitions have always been for educational purposes. While the score goes away, you still get to keep what you learned. (\\u2026or you can always re-submit!) Besides, with a public ground truth and never-ending timeline, it was never the case that getting-started leaderboards were an honest representation of merit.\\n\\nHave fun and happy modeling!\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309319\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-02-22T21:57:31.459085500Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-03T10:21:54.053333300Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023757Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 309535,\n    \"title\": \"Spaceship Titanic Compare BaseModels EveryBody Get Insight!\",\n    \"author\": \"Wongi Park\",\n    \"author_username\": \"kalelpark\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"MASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 21,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"SpaceShip Titanic Each Data has multiple NaN Values.\\nI'm use pycarret and use fillna method = ffill.\\nMake BaseModel. (This is always not 100% Correct)\\nBut. It will give you Insight to create the model!\\nI hope This Discussion helps you!\\n\\nTop5 Model\\n- Gradient Boosting Classifier    - 79.6%\\n- CatBoost   - 79.6%\\n- Ada Boost Classifier  - 79.4%\\n- Random Forest  - 79.2%\\n- Light GBM   - 79.1%\\n\\n<a href=\\\"https://ibb.co/pPcXwqd\\\"><img src=\\\"https://i.ibb.co/26xKhJd/2022-02-24-094651.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"2022-02-24-094651\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></a>\\n\\n\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309535\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-02-24T00:57:22.744746900Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2023-08-02T17:48:44.053333300Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023766Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 509041,\n    \"title\": \"Starting materials and references - AutoML episode 2\",\n    \"author\": \"Ravi Ramakrishnan\",\n    \"author_username\": \"ravi20076\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"GRANDMASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 20,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"Hello all,\\n\\nHope this post finds you well. Wishing you the best for the month's Playground challenge and the 2nd episode of the AutoML challenge. \\n\\nI have compiled the below resources for the auto ML component of the episode and hope that they are useful.\\n\\n## General references - auto ML kernels from Kaggle\\n\\n### FLAML\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/rzatemizel/flaml-ensemble-ladregression\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/gauravduttakiit/pumpkin-classification-flaml-ndcg\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/paddykb/ps-s3e14-flaml-bfi-be-bop-a-blueberry-do-dah\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/rohanrao/automl-tutorial-tps-september-2021\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/andreshg/automl-libraries-comparison\\n6. https://www.kaggle.com/code/sanjaylalwani/autism-diagnosis-with-flaml\\n7. https://www.kaggle.com/code/gauravduttakiit/raisin-classification-flaml-ndcg\\n8. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mmkuznecov/tabnet-catboost-flaml\\n9. https://www.kaggle.com/code/paddykb/ps-s3e11-flaml-bfi-brute-force-ignorance\\n10. https://www.kaggle.com/code/bennyfung/multi-class-obesity-flaml\\n\\n### H2O.ai\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mlandry/random-forest-example\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/frankmollard/h2o-machine-learning\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/tunguz/ieee-with-h2o-automl\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/pranav84/surprise-me-h2o-automl-version\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/couyang/wine-eda-dt-rf-xgb-lightgbm-svm-and-h2o\\n6. https://www.kaggle.com/code/akshat0007/learning-h20-iris-dataset\\n7. https://www.kaggle.com/code/parulpandey/the-emergence-of-automl\\n8. https://www.kaggle.com/code/itspavansatish/auto-ml-h20\\n9. https://www.kaggle.com/code/anitharajamani/spaceship-titanic-using-auto-ml-h20\\n10. https://www.kaggle.com/code/satyaprakashshukl/h20-wids-datathon-2024-challenge\\n\\n### PyCaret\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/frtgnn/pycaret-introduction-classification-regression\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/junhyeok99/automl-pycaret\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/arootda/pycaret-visualization-optimization-0-81\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/songulerdem/energy-consumption-forecasting-with-pycaret\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/caesarmario/credit-card-approval-prediction-w-pycaret\\n\\n### AutoGluon\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/kdmitrie/pgs41-just-few-lines-of-autogluon\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/bennyfung/easy-to-use-automl-autogluon-flaml-autosklearn\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/kdmitrie/pgs41-more-lines-of-autogluon\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/lucamassaron/autogluon-for-tabular-playground-sep-2021\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mozattt/titanic-by-automl-autogluon-quick-start\\n6. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mfmfmf3/autogluon-starter\\n7. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mountpotatoq/autogluon-finetune-solutions\\n8. https://www.kaggle.com/code/innixma/autogluon-rapids-top-1\\n\\n### LightAutoML\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/simakov/lama-tabularautoml-preset-example\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mukaseevru/tps-mar-22-fe-lama-lightautoml\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mikita1580/tabular-playground-sep-lama\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mukaseevru/tps-jun-22-lama-lightautoml-in-loop\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/cv13j0/pss-3-episode-3-lama\\n6. https://www.kaggle.com/code/alexryzhkov/n3-tps-april-21-lightautoml-starter\\n7. https://www.kaggle.com/code/alexryzhkov/lightautoml-interpretable-model-autowoe\\n8. https://www.kaggle.com/code/alexryzhkov/smoking-lama-lightautoml-baseline\\n9. https://www.kaggle.com/code/alexryzhkov/lightautoml-baseline-tps-june-2021\\n10. https://www.kaggle.com/code/alexryzhkov/lightautoml-extreme-short-titanic-solution\\n\\n### Bluecast\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thomasmeiner/ps4e2-eda-feature-engineering-modelling\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thomasmeiner/ps4e1-eda-feature-engineering-modelling\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thomasmeiner/birth-weight-with-bluecast\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thomasmeiner/ps4e1-bluecast-0-90\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thomasmeiner/ps3e24-bluecast-eda-automl-tracking\\n\\n### TPOT\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/fathyfathysahlool/tpot-classifier\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/prishasawhney/steel-plate-defect-detection-s4e3-using-tpot\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/yousefmohamed20/spaceship-titanic\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thebrownviking20/tpot-a-great-tool-to-automate-your-ml-workflow\\n\\n## Top solutions- AutoML edition 1- May2024\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/500700 -- rank1\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/499725 -- rank3\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/501123 -- rank4\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/500453 -- rank5\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/499602 -- rank6\\n6. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/499507 -- rank7\\n7. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/499494 -- rank8\\n8. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/500783 -- rank9\\n9. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/499550 -- rank10\\n\\nI have uploaded the original data [here](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ravi20076/playgrounds4e06originaldata). Please feel free to use it as part of your pipeline too. \\n\\nWishing you the best for the competition! Happy learning and best regards.\\nRavi Ramakrishnan\\n\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/509041\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2024-06-01T00:15:47.515639Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2024-06-01T03:56:15.016666700Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023775Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 523408,\n    \"title\": \"References- AutoML episode\",\n    \"author\": \"Ravi Ramakrishnan\",\n    \"author_username\": \"ravi20076\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"GRANDMASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 20,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"Hello all,\\n\\nHope this post finds you well. Wishing you the best for the month's Playground challenge and the concurrent episode of the AutoML challenge. \\nI have compiled the below resources for the auto ML component of the episode and hope that they are useful.\\n\\n## Top solutions- AutoML edition 1- May2024\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/500700 \\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/499725 \\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/501123 \\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/500453 \\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/499602\\n6. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/499507\\n7. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/499494 \\n8. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/500783 \\n9. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e5/discussion/499550 \\n\\n## Top solutions- AutoML edition 2- June2024 (not sorted by rank)\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/509631\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/509316 \\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/510081\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/509510\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/509937\\n6. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/509642 \\n7. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/509644\\n8. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/509665\\n9. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/510614\\n10. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/510409\\n11. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/509710\\n12. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e6/discussion/511712\\n\\n## Top solutions- AutoML edition 3- July2024 (not sorted by rank)\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e7/discussion/516475\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e7/discussion/516265\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e7/discussion/517112\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e7/discussion/516855\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e7/discussion/516963\\n6. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e7/discussion/517079\\n7. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e7/discussion/518542\\n8. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e7/discussion/518573\\n9. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e7/discussion/518567\\n10. https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e7/discussion/516860 -- must read in my opinion\\n\\n## General references - auto ML kernels from Kaggle across use-cases\\n\\n### PyCaret\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/frtgnn/pycaret-introduction-classification-regression\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/junhyeok99/automl-pycaret\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/arootda/pycaret-visualization-optimization-0-81\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/songulerdem/energy-consumption-forecasting-with-pycaret\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/caesarmario/credit-card-approval-prediction-w-pycaret\\n\\n### FLAML\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/rzatemizel/flaml-ensemble-ladregression\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/gauravduttakiit/pumpkin-classification-flaml-ndcg\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/paddykb/ps-s3e14-flaml-bfi-be-bop-a-blueberry-do-dah\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/rohanrao/automl-tutorial-tps-september-2021\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/andreshg/automl-libraries-comparison\\n\\n### H2O.ai\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mlandry/random-forest-example\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/frankmollard/h2o-machine-learning\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/tunguz/ieee-with-h2o-automl\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/pranav84/surprise-me-h2o-automl-version\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/couyang/wine-eda-dt-rf-xgb-lightgbm-svm-and-h2o\\n\\n### AutoGluon\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/kdmitrie/pgs41-just-few-lines-of-autogluon\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/bennyfung/easy-to-use-automl-autogluon-flaml-autosklearn\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/kdmitrie/pgs41-more-lines-of-autogluon\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/lucamassaron/autogluon-for-tabular-playground-sep-2021\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mozattt/titanic-by-automl-autogluon-quick-start\\n\\n\\n### LightAutoML\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/simakov/lama-tabularautoml-preset-example\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mukaseevru/tps-mar-22-fe-lama-lightautoml\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mikita1580/tabular-playground-sep-lama\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/mukaseevru/tps-jun-22-lama-lightautoml-in-loop\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/cv13j0/pss-3-episode-3-lama\\n\\n\\n### Bluecast\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thomasmeiner/ps4e2-eda-feature-engineering-modelling\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thomasmeiner/ps4e1-eda-feature-engineering-modelling\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thomasmeiner/birth-weight-with-bluecast\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thomasmeiner/ps4e1-bluecast-0-90\\n5. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thomasmeiner/ps3e24-bluecast-eda-automl-tracking\\n\\n### TPOT\\n1. https://www.kaggle.com/code/fathyfathysahlool/tpot-classifier\\n2. https://www.kaggle.com/code/prishasawhney/steel-plate-defect-detection-s4e3-using-tpot\\n3. https://www.kaggle.com/code/yousefmohamed20/spaceship-titanic\\n4. https://www.kaggle.com/code/thebrownviking20/tpot-a-great-tool-to-automate-your-ml-workflow\\n\\nWishing you all the best for the current AutoML episode and best regards!\\n\\nP.S. \\nKindly name your submission files according to the [link here](https://www.kaggle.com/automl-grand-prix) for the AutoML version of this episode!\\n\\nBest regards,\\nRavi Ramakrishnan\\n\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/523408\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2024-08-01T00:26:50.903106900Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2024-08-03T13:33:58.960Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023790Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 335874,\n    \"title\": \"Interesting ways to fill NULL Values - Improving accuracy by ~2%\",\n    \"author\": \"Praveen Kumar\",\n    \"author_username\": \"inboxpraveen17\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"CONTRIBUTOR\",\n    \"votes\": 18,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"During my data analysis phase, I discovered the following, more practical ways to fulfill Null values, at least to some specific features.\\n\\n**HomePlanet:** Instead of directly it to be earth, you and feature engineer null values based on the following 2 scenarios.\\ni) People who are travelling as a group, are more likely to come from the same home planet. Thus, if you find missing values within the same group, it's better to fill them based on group values. \\nii) People who are not traveling in a group, are not 100% to come from Earth. So, instead, you can look at the probability distribution of different home planets, and fill the remaining null values based on the normal distribution. This will additionally maintain consistency in data rather than creating bias.\\n**CryoSleep, Destination & VIP can be filled in a similar manner**\\n\\n \\nAdditionally, people have combined 'RoomService, FoodCourt, shopping mall, Spa, VRDeck' into a single column by adding each value. However, 'RoomService & FoodCourt' are essentials for a living but not \\\"shopping mall, Spa & VRDeck\\\". So, these features can be split into 2 features. People who spend more on living essentials seem to be richer, thus having higher status among all the people onboard. \\n\\n\\nBringing practical intuition into machine learning could give you better results.\\nHope this helps. \",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/335874\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-07-08T08:53:37.493441800Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2024-10-27T13:32:33.070Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023800Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 551259,\n    \"title\": \"Some more tabular competitions with relevant use-cases \",\n    \"author\": \"Ravi Ramakrishnan\",\n    \"author_username\": \"ravi20076\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"GRANDMASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 15,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"Hello all,\\n\\nThis post is in continuation of the post [here](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/playground-series-s4e12/discussion/550868) that directs you to consider a recently started Kaggle featured competition for survival analysis. Here, I wish to posit 4-5 additional options that you could consider for your own learning and development. All of them are tabular and have manageable datasets for one to start off-\\n\\n| Competition |  Overview page| ML topic | Close date | \\n| --- | --- | ----------- | ------------- | \\n| Child Mind Institute \\u2014 Problematic Internet Use | https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/child-mind-institute-problematic-internet-use | Ordinal regression | 20Dec2024| \\n| Jane Street Real-Time Market Data Forecasting| https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/child-mind-institute-problematic-internet-use | Time series for financial assets | 14Jan2025 | \\n| Spaceship Titanic ...in all probability| https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic-in-all-probability | Classifier with calibration | 16Dec2024 | \\n| Storm Nowcasting Hackathon - IndabaX Madagascar 24| https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/hackathon-DL-IndabaX-MDG-2024 | Binary Classifier | 15Dec2024 | \\n| Neo bank churn prediction| https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/neo-bank-non-sub-churn-prediction |  Classifier | 31Jan2025 | \\n| Rohlik Sales Forecasting Challenge| https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/rohlik-sales-forecasting-challenge-v2 |  Time series forecasting | 15Feb2025 | \\n| Physical Activity Clustering| https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/physical-activity-clustering/overview |  Classifier | 01Jan2026 | \\n\\n<br>I can recommend these competitions to one and all looking for some diversity in their learning and development and are looking for some different use-cases as well.\\n\\nBest regards!\\n\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/551259\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2024-12-12T05:47:25.674325800Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2024-12-15T08:15:14.870Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023827Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 309626,\n    \"title\": \"\\ud83d\\udccc EDA\\ud83d\\udcc8 + FE\\ud83d\\udd25 + Comparison\\u2696\\ufe0f + Pseudo\\ud83c\\udfad\",\n    \"author\": \"Hasan Basri Ak\\u00e7ay\",\n    \"author_username\": \"hasanbasriakcay\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"GRANDMASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 15,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"Hi all,\\n\\nI prepared three notebooks for you. In the first [notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/hasanbasriakcay/spaceship-titanic-eda-fe-baseline), I did exploratory data analysis and feature engineering. In the second [notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/hasanbasriakcay/spaceship-titanic-pycaret-model-comparisons), I compared machine learning models and in the third [notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/hasanbasriakcay/spaceship-titanic-pseudo-labels-stacking), I did pseudo labeling for better Leaderboard scores. \\n\\n1.  [EDA Notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/hasanbasriakcay/spaceship-titanic-eda-fe-baseline)\\n2. [Model Comparisons Notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/hasanbasriakcay/spaceship-titanic-pycaret-model-comparisons)\\n3. [Pseudo Labels Notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/hasanbasriakcay/spaceship-titanic-pseudo-labels-stacking)\\n\\nKindly upvote if you find it useful \\ud83d\\ude0a\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/309626\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-02-24T13:58:31.346542Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2023-08-15T11:41:08.910Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023853Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 462302,\n    \"title\": \"predict Vs predict_proba methods\",\n    \"author\": \"Carl McBride Ellis\",\n    \"author_username\": \"carlmcbrideellis\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"GRANDMASTER\",\n    \"votes\": 14,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"### `predict()` Vs `predict_proba()`\\n<br>\\n\\nBoth the `train.csv` and the `test.csv` datasets in this competition are the very same as those in the standard [Spaceship Titanic](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic) competition so EDA work is pretty much transferable. \\n\\nHowever, a significant difference is the `submission.csv`. In both the *Titanic* and the *Spaceship Titanic* one is using the accuracy score, which is based on binary predictions hence the use of the [**`predict`** method](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/glossary.html#term-predict). In this competition, using the Brier score, we would do better using the [**`predict_proba`** method](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/glossary.html#term-predict_proba) which returns the confidence in a prediction (I am hesitant to say the actual probability associated with a prediction, perhaps more like a score). Note that, as well as many of the scikit-learn classifiers,  [XGBoost](https://xgboost.readthedocs.io/en/stable/python/python_api.html#xgboost.XGBClassifier.predict_proba), [LightGBM](https://lightgbm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/pythonapi/lightgbm.LGBMClassifier.html#lightgbm.LGBMClassifier.predict_proba) and [CatBoost](https://catboost.ai/en/docs/concepts/python-reference_catboostclassifier_predict_proba) also provide `predict_proba` methods.\\n\\nUsage example: for \\\"probabilities\\\"\\n\\n```python\\npredictions = classifier.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]\\n```\\n\\nrather than the following for classes\\n\\n```python\\npredictions = classifier.predict(X_test)\\n```\\nI hope this helps!\\n\\n\\nAll the best,\\ncarl\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/462302\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2023-12-19T10:13:14.206707900Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2023-12-25T10:24:14.536666700Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023862Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"competition_id\": \"spaceship-titanic\",\n    \"discussion_id\": 312173,\n    \"title\": \"Tip. Increase your score!\",\n    \"author\": \"Manhow\",\n    \"author_username\": \"michael6141\",\n    \"author_tier\": \"CONTRIBUTOR\",\n    \"votes\": 14,\n    \"comment_count\": 0,\n    \"body_markdown\": \"Everybody looking for an idea on how to increase your score I dedicate this topic. Being a novice I found a method that allows me to stay in top 10 (10.03.2022). Try to average received probabilities on each validation split (list(probabilities)/len(probabilities)), predict_proba may help you. Averaging the model is a powerful tool to get a high validation score.\\ud83d\\udcaf\\ud83d\\ude42\",\n    \"url\": \"https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/312173\",\n    \"tags\": [],\n    \"created_at\": \"2022-03-10T18:10:06.170209800Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2023-08-15T11:37:50.530Z\",\n    \"last_fetched_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.235323+00:00\",\n    \"ingested_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:20:09.023871Z\"\n  }\n]\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
