d in database.\nв•­в”Ђ Make the best use of \"Deck\" feature в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•®\nв”‚ Author: Mostafa Alaa | Votes: 9 | Comments: 0 | Created: 2022-02-28          в”‚\nв”‚ https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/spaceship-titanic/discussion/310238      в”‚\nв•°в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•Ї\n\nDealing with Deck will not be the better deal win you set each letter on it a   \nnumber such as A -> 1 and so on, instead, you can plot them to see who is the   \nletters with the highest ratio to transporting (danger decks) and put them in a \nfeature such as any deck with one of these letters get zero else 1. Don't make  \nit with \"safe decks\" it will not make your score higher I tested this.          \n\nв”Ђв”Ђ 2 Comments в”Ђв”Ђ\n\nOmikumar Bhavinkumar Makadia 2023-08-16\nThanks for the tip !                                                            \n\nNick Kipshidze 2025-01-06\nHere's a little hacky code I wrote to separate some cabin values. Maybe someone \nwill find it useful:                                                            \n\n                                                                                \n df = pd.read_csv(\"./train.csv\")                                                \n df[\"Deck\"] = df[\"Cabin\"].str.split(\"/\").str[0]                                 \n df[\"Num\"] = df[\"Cabin\"].str.split(\"/\").str[1].astype(dtype=float)              \n df[\"Side\"] = df[\"Cabin\"].str.split(\"/\").str[2].replace(to_replace=[\"P\", \"S\"],  \n value=[0, 1])                                                                  \n                                                                                \n\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
